@itsazzad:
Please see https://github.com/blueimp/jQuery-File-Upload#support

@blueimp We plan to use jQuery-File-Upload via composer package manager not for server side implementation, but for client-side one. That's how we can keep your plugin as an external dependency and have an up-to-date version of the plugin.
Proposed PR does not require updating `composer.json` after each release. Composer will handle it automatically. All you need is to register at https://packagist.org/ and add a service hook to the Github.
Thanks in advance

